<subSubSection id="C303A4DDFFFEE571E56E0AC1B21A2DC9" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA6F756FFFEE571E56E0AC1B5CD2F8A" blockId="22.[813,1456,1428,2030]" box="[813,913,1428,1454]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA6F756FFFEE571E56E0AE0B21A2DC9" blockId="22.[813,1456,1428,2030]" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">
<bibRefCitation id="EF888AA7FFFEE571E56E0AE0B5A32FE8" author="Schmalfuss" box="[813,1023,1461,1487]" firstAuthor="Schmalfuss" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" pagination="143 - 151" refId="ref12103" refString="SCHMALFUSS H. 2008. - The terrestrial isopod genus Schizidium (Isopoda: Oniscidea): systematics, distribution, morphology. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, A, Neue Serie 1: 143 - 151." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmalfuss (2008)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that all the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E3C90AE0B5942FC8" authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1833" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Armadillidiidae</taxonomicName>
possessing a schisma on the pereonite 1 (
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E5750AA0B2362C28" authority="Budde-Lund, 1885" authorityName="Budde-Lund" authorityYear="1885" box="[822,1130,1524,1551]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Eluma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E5750AA0B5232C28" box="[822,895,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Eluma</emphasis>
Budde-Lund, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E23B0AA0B3F62C28" authority="Vandel, 1961" authorityName="Vandel" authorityYear="1961" box="[1144,1450,1525,1551]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Ballodillium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E23B0AA0B35F2C28" box="[1144,1283,1525,1551]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Ballodillium</emphasis>
Vandel, 1961
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E51D0941B5A22C09" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1919" box="[862,1022,1556,1582]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Alloschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E51D0941B5A22C09" box="[862,1022,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Alloschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) fall within his definition of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E56E0961B2022C68" authority="Verhoeff, 1901" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1901" box="[813,1118,1588,1615]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Schizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E56E0961B5F42C69" box="[813,936,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Schizidium</emphasis>
Verhoeff, 1901
</taxonomicName>
. However, he was not certain that all these genera belong to a monophyletic group and the presence of the schisma might be due to convergence. Therefore, he kept 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E5B709C1B2372C89" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1901" box="[1012,1131,1684,1710]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Schizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E5B709C1B2372C89" box="[1012,1131,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Schizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate genus distributed from 
<collectingCountry id="F30EB7C6FFFEE571E52B09E1B5EF2CE9" box="[872,947,1716,1742]" name="Greece" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Greece</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F30EB7C6FFFEE571E59709E0B2592CE8" box="[980,1029,1717,1743]" name="Iran" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Iran</collectingCountry>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E2C209E1B3412CE9" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1919" box="[1153,1309,1716,1742]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Alloschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E2C209E1B3412CE9" box="[1153,1309,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Alloschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E58C0981B2292CC9" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1919" box="[975,1141,1748,1774]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E58C0981B2292CC9" box="[975,1141,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Paraschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a possible synapomorphic character for these two genera being the subovoidal, instead of spherical, shape of the ball when the animals roll up (see also discussion in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF888AA7FFFEE571E2050866B3712D6A" author="Taiti &amp; Ferrara" box="[1094,1325,1843,1870]" firstAuthor="Taiti" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" pagination="727 - 732" refId="ref11392" refString="FERRARA F. &amp; TAITI S. 1996. - Typhlarmadillidium ruffoi nuova specie di isopodo terrestre dei Colli Euganei (Padova) (Crustacea, Oniscidea, Armadillidiidae). Bollettino del Museo civico di Storia naturale di Verona 20: 727 - 732." type="journal article" year="1996">Taiti &amp; Ferrara 1996</bibRefCitation>
). Then, the autapomorphic characters for 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E2CD0806B36F2D4A" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1919" box="[1166,1331,1875,1901]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Alloschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E2CD0806B36F2D4A" box="[1166,1331,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Alloschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared with 
<taxonomicName id="4C198CD5FFFEE571E5280826B2442DAA" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1919" box="[875,1048,1907,1933]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96D2B44FFFEE571E5280826B2442DAA" box="[875,1048,1907,1933]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="217">Paraschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the presence of the schisma. As remarked by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF888AA7FFFEE571E5FC08C6B2CC2D89" author="Schmalfuss" box="[959,1168,1939,1966]" firstAuthor="Schmalfuss" pageId="22" pageNumber="217" pagination="143 - 151" refId="ref12103" refString="SCHMALFUSS H. 2008. - The terrestrial isopod genus Schizidium (Isopoda: Oniscidea): systematics, distribution, morphology. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, A, Neue Serie 1: 143 - 151." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmalfuss (2008)</bibRefCitation>
a molecular investigation might help to clarify the interrelationships among all the above mentioned genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
